  ceases or following the last ECB pension payment to the pensioner or
  their entitled dependants.   3. Exception: The 10‑year maximum
  applies only "provided that there are no pending claims"; if pending
  claims exist, retention may be extended.   4. Related points and
  competent authorities: medical certificates/medical files are
  retained separately by the ECB’s Medical Adviser and do not form
  part of the personal file; the Directorate General Human Resources
  holds the personal file, and the Chief Services Officer (acting on
  behalf of the Executive Board) may approve disclosure to third
  parties.   5. Specific document removal: Certain documents (for
  example, some appraisal/underperformance documents) are subject to
