Question: What is the mileage rate paid for daily local transportation between a
  child's home and school under the education allowance?
Example answer: Provided there is a distance of more than one kilometre between the
  home closest to the school and the educational establishment
  attended, the rate paid shall be EUR 0.40 per kilometre. The mileage
  fee is paid monthly using the formula (km × 2 × 0.40 EUR × 180
  school days) ÷ 12. (ECB Staff Rules, pages 67–68)
