Question: I think I'm being targeted with inappropriate behaviour by a
  colleague. What informal options do I have before formally
  reporting, and how long do I have to request protection if I later
  face retaliation for reporting?
Example answer: Members of staff who consider themselves the target of inappropriate
  behaviour, or who have witnessed it, may seek informal support from
  a trusted person of their choice (including a staff representative
  or a counterpart in DG Human Resources), a Social Counsellor, or the
  Mediator, and shall not suffer any negative consequences for doing
  so unless they are later found to have made deliberately false or
  malicious statements. If retaliation occurs, whistleblowers and
  witnesses may submit a request for protection from retaliation to
  the Chief Compliance and Governance Officer within 24 months from
  the time of the occurrence of the alleged retaliation. (ECB Staff
  Rules, pages 22, 27)
