  seek early resolution by consulting: (a) a trusted person of their
  choice (including a staff representative or a counterpart in the
  Directorate General Human Resources), (b) a Social Counsellor, or
  (c) the Mediator. Early-resolution attempts shall not give rise to
  negative consequences for the staff member unless they make
  deliberately false or malicious statements. In addition, members of
  staff may request interim support measures from the Director General
  Human Resources or their Deputy (Article 0.4bis.1a context; Article
  0.4bis.1a.3; p.22).    2. Time limit to request protection if later
  subject to retaliation: A request for protection from retaliation
  must be submitted within 24 months from the time of the occurrence
